# Feature analysis (phase 1)

Part of the mandatory [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc). **Do not write production or test code** until phases 1–4 are complete for the current changelog entry.

**Answering feature questions (FQ*n*) updates the feature doc only** — it is not development approval. **Each answer triggers a mandatory impact review** — see [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) § Impact review when answering open questions.

After phase 1, **every feature change** proceeds to phase 2 (architecture design) — [architecture-design.mdc](architecture-design.mdc).

Template: [feature/README.md](../../feature/README.md).

## When required

| Trigger | Analysis required |
|---------|-------------------|
| New behaviour, API, UI route, schema | Yes — create or extend `feature/<feature-slug>.md` |
| Refactor touching multiple packages or bounded contexts | Yes |
| Bug fix with cross-feature side effects | Yes — append changelog entry |
| Typo, comment-only, formatter, docs-only (no behaviour) | No — exempt from full process |

When feature analysis is required, **architecture design (phase 2) is also required** — no exceptions.

## Process

### 0. Resolve `<feature-slug>` (before creating the file)

The slug names a **high-level capability or user-facing feature**, not a single task or implementation step.

| Good (capability) | Bad (task or implementation) |
|-------------------|------------------------------|
| `ticket-import` | `fix-csv-parser-bug` |
| `account-settings` | `add-password-field-validation` |
| `kanban-board` | `refactor-drag-drop-handler` |

**Extract the slug**

1. **Name the capability** — what product area or feature-catalog row does this belong to? (e.g. Import tickets, Account settings, Kanban board).
2. **Derive slug** — 2–4 words, kebab-case, noun phrase; align with [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) feature names or bounded context when possible.
3. **Search for a related feature doc** — before creating a new file:
   - List `feature/*.md` (exclude `README.md`).
   - Skim summaries and changelog titles in existing files.
   - Cross-check [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) and [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) for the same capability.
4. **Decide**

   | Finding | Action |
   |---------|--------|
   | Clear match to an existing `feature/<slug>.md` | **Extend** that file — add a changelog entry; refresh Impact only if footprint changed |
   | No related doc; capability is distinct | **Create** `feature/<feature-slug>.md` |
   | Multiple candidates or unclear fit | **Stop and ask** — present 2–3 options (extend existing vs new slug). **Do not assume.** |

**When in doubt, ask.** Examples that require user confirmation: bug fix vs new sub-capability; refactor spanning two features; request could extend `ticket-import` or belong under `kanban-board`.

### 1. Create or open `feature/<feature-slug>.md`

Kebab-case slug, stable for the lifetime of the capability. Re-run step 0 if the request grows into a different feature area.

### 2. Impact — document scope before coding

- Bounded contexts and packages ([issues-bounded-contexts.mdc](issues-bounded-contexts.mdc))
- **Wireframe** — `## Wireframe` section with layouts for every UI route, dialog, shell widget, or email template; revise on scope change
- API / OpenAPI / Angular surfaces (high level — detailed design in phase 2 **Architecture**)
- Schema (`V1.0.0__Database_Creation.sql`), seed data, migrations (high level)
- Tests and docs to update
- Risks (optional bullets) and **Feature questions (FQ*n***)** table with status `open` | `answered` | `not valid` and **Answer** column

**Architecture questions (AQ*n***)** belong in phase 2 — do not mix product scope into the AQ table or technical trade-offs into the FQ table.

**When a feature question is answered:** run impact review per [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) § Impact review when answering open questions — refresh Impact, changelog cross-impacts, Risks, **Wireframe**, **Feature checklist**, and domain spec; add new **FQ*n*** or **AQ*n*** if the answer surfaces gaps.

Increment **Feature version** when adding a changelog entry; assign the next sequential **Version** to that entry.

### 3. Changelog — one entry per discrete change request (append; do not rewrite history)

- **Change name** — short title (e.g. `Add ticket CSV export`)
- **Status** — `planned` (then `architecture-ready` → `tasks-ready` → `approved` → `in-progress` → `done` per [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc))
- **Impact on other features** — list affected capabilities, routes, or contexts; write `None identified` when isolated
- **Feature checklist** — start in phase 1 on the changelog entry (**FC1**, **FC2**, …); verifiable scope, behaviour, wireframe, and doc criteria — see [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) § Phase 1 and § Feature checklist recheck
- **Wireframe** — top-level `## Wireframe` on the feature doc; guides phase 5 UI implementation

Phases 2–5 (architecture design, task break, approval, TDD) continue in the same changelog entry — see [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc). **Order is mandatory:** architecture design before task break; task break before approval; approval before any `src/main` or `src/test` edit.

## Allowed edits by phase

| Phase | Status | May edit |
|-------|--------|----------|
| 1 | `planned` | `feature/*.md`, `docs/**`, domain spec (incl. **Wireframe**, initial **Feature checklist**, **FQ*n*** table) |
| 1 (FQ answered) | `planned`, `architecture-ready`, or `tasks-ready` | Same — **not** application source |
| 2 | `planned` → `architecture-ready` | `feature/*.md` (**Architecture**, **AQ*n*** table, Impact, domain spec) — [architecture-design.mdc](architecture-design.mdc) |
| 3 | `tasks-ready` | `feature/*.md` (Feature checklist, Tasks, Test coverage) |
| 4 | `approved` | `feature/*.md` (Development approval line) |
| 5 | `in-progress` / `done` | `src/main/**`, `src/test/**`, `src/main/webui/**`, docs |

## Order with other gates

```
Feature analysis → architecture design → domain spec review → task break → development approved → TDD → verify
```

Domain checklist: [domain-model.mdc](domain-model.mdc). Architecture: [architecture-design.mdc](architecture-design.mdc). TDD: [issues-model.mdc](issues-model.mdc).

## During implementation (phase 5 only)

- Mark changelog entry status through the lifecycle (`approved` → `in-progress` → `done`).
- Check off **Tasks** and **Test coverage** items as completed; update **Feature checklist** as criteria are verified; keep **Wireframe** and **Architecture** in sync when scope changes.
- **Before `done`:** run mandatory **Feature checklist recheck** — see [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) § Phase 5.
- **Working code invariant:** fix or revert before stopping; never mark `done` on red — see [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) § Working code invariant.
- If scope grows, add tasks and obtain new approval — do not expand silently.

## After implementation

Close the loop in the same changelog entry (**Implementation notes**, tests run). User-facing doc updates remain in [documentation.mdc](documentation.mdc) — do not duplicate route tables in feature docs.

## Legacy open questions

Existing feature docs may use undifferentiated **Q*n***. Treat them as **FQ*n*** until the doc is updated. Split or renumber into **FQ*n*** / **AQ*n*** when editing that feature file.
